cs.NE, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper introduces an extension to the Multi-dimensional Archive of Phenotypic Elites (MAP-Elites) algorithm that addresses its limitation in scaling to high-dimensional feature spaces. The algorithm uses a centroidal Voronoi tessellation (CVT) to partition the feature space into a desired number of regions. This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:

- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes an extension to an evolutionary algorithm, MAP-Elites, to improve its scalability in high-dimensional feature spaces. This falls under the scope of neural and evolutionary computing.
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper demonstrates the effectiveness of the new algorithm in maze navigation and hexapod locomotion tasks, which are robotics-related applications.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a machine learning algorithm, MAP-Elites, and introduces an extension to improve its scalability.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an algorithm that falls under the scope of artificial intelligence, as it involves evolutionary computation and optimization.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper's focus on improving the scalability of an algorithm for robotics-related applications falls under the scope of systems and control.
